flowRoot.flowPara: If you are looking for a candidate with knowledge of informatics, bioengineering and natural scientist, look no further. Leaving the cliches aside, I have experience working with scientific data, using different programmatic tools to extract, transform and analyse data, and provide a meaningful representation of the information in the data. Furthermore, I have some knowledge in system administration and network operations. I have worked in one of the biggest CROs, plus I have academic experience abroad. As you can see, I have an understanding of the IT, Health care and the Scientific sectors. What is more important I have the desire to work exactly with data in the Health care sector, something that I understand your RWE team is doing. Invite me for an interview and I will further prove to you I am the right candidate for one of the position and if there is something that I am lacking behind technically I will push myself to learn it.
Interdisciplinary field of study oriented towards statistical analysis of biological data and designing systems for processing of biological and medical data. Study focus:
Scientific Software Development;
Object Oriented Programming;
Relational Databases, DBMS and Scientific Databases;
Statistics and Biostatistics;
Web Development;
Computer Aided Drug Design (CADD);
Interdisciplinary field of study, requiring expertise within physics, chemistry, biology, biotechnology, mathematics, and material science.
Study focus:
Protein engineering and self-assembly;
Biochemical and Biophysical processes in proteins;
Self-organizing systems;
Physics and Chemistry of Surfaces;
Melecular Dynamics (MD) Simulations;
Organic molecules in nanomachines and nanoelectronics;
Providing help in clinical trials projects start-up activities;
Cooperated with different departments and initiating clinical trial projects;
Using Excel and proprietary data and analytics platform for analysis of project data;
Responsible for coordination of a team constituted of me and another specialist;
Providing support (software and hardware), maintenance and expansion of computer stations and LAN in the Faculty of Biology;
Collaboration with the University Center for Information and Communication Technologies to ensure smooth workflow of the university network and services;
Deployment of a Help Desk System;
Incident ownership - Investigation, Diagnosis and Resolution;
Part of the reactive service team;
Escalation of high priority incidents;
Following ITIL processes, procedures, tasks for incident management;
